The paper proposes a new active learning technique based on query synthesis using InfoGAN, which is a generative model. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method is applied to image datasets, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-categories of Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Natural Language Processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper uses a feedback mechanism to decide which datapoints to query, which is a characteristic of active learning, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
